  "commentary": "With SPX at 6993 sitting just below the massive +17.6B gamma wall at 7000, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level while the -3.6% 1-min move suggests we're seeing that resistance in real-time. The PIN regime with 119.97B total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, where dealers will provide liquidity by selling this bounce and buying any dips toward the 6877 flip level. Watch 7000 as the key inflection - failure to break above should trigger dealer selling into the thick positive gamma cluster at 7025/7050, while any break below 6877 flips dealers short gamma and removes the stabilizing bid.\n\nBottom line: expect strong resistance at 7000 with downside bias toward 6900.",
